        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 3:57AM CDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 357 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Sutton Bay Rec Area, or 14 miles northwest of Onida, moving east at
25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Gettysburg, Agar, Gorman, Sutton Bay Rec Area, and Cottonwood Lake
Near Agar.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
